    <items>
        <item id="i63a1243108529237735fed37f1a9dc87e">
            <label key="895241da0e2c73af7515e6507c997b7d">
                <text>Do electric vehicles emit less CO<sub>2</sub> per kilometre of driving than vehicles that use fossil fuels?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="93cba07454f06a4a960172bbd6e2a435">
                <text>Yes</text>
            </label>
            <label key="bafd7322c6e97d25b6299b5d6fe8920b">
                <text>No</text>
            </label>
            <label key="321777133075cda474631c062196d935">
                <text>Use the data in the table to support your answer.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i63a124434038f280950ef57a03729bbac">
            <label key="3b5e86c6b3b09ea89039a30c37ed16cc">
                <text>The table shows the amount of CO<sub>2</sub> emitted by cars and by the production of the cars’ fuel.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="d80c7c8bee360720462165f4fff1b3c0">
                <text>Which one of the following factors should also be considered in determining the total CO<sub>2</sub> emissions of car use?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="6f6e6a7056eecb1c670114e921fa0a07">
                <text>energy released by combustion of the fuel</text>
            </label>
            <label key="6bdb4ee89ad6d733546bf75ada9c7289">
                <text>energy consumed by using the headlights</text>
            </label>
            <label key="3f34c3fe84cbbd7422b827aded65b49f">
                <text>energy converted by applying the brakes</text>
            </label>
            <label key="eb15fe6030308d4ccee55c6f20813771">
                <text>energy used in the manufacture of the car</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i63a1245d6c7e02380687cd0fbea5698ed">
            <label key="8175fb2c7b150644279f5d9e3b7c14b1">
                <text>Electric cars use electricity from energy that is stored in a battery pack. The production of these battery packs requires electricity that is generated from fossil fuels such as coal.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="b37690b5f776725b64dc473b68072be9">
                <text>Which action would reduce the CO<sub>2</sub> released from the production of the battery packs by the greatest amount?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="9bbad6ccb9a86a0ea55ba11e04891855">
                <text>Increase the amount of electricity generated from burning natural gas.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="b3dc0f5ec84fd4e5fee9822d94839b01">
                <text>Increase the amount of energy the car battery pack can store.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="cb8434a1c94024077a7be02c0b834179">
                <text>Increase the distance the car can travel before the battery needs to be recharged.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="539f1c2ad5375776ae772cada225bc85">
                <text>Increase the efficiency of energy conversion at coal-burning power stations.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i63a126c24f0b8143618a43edc45d17e5c4">
            <label key="82cae3c6eb0bb168541a7a93b145ed3d">
                <text>Changing from fossil-fuel cars to electric cars can create other problems that need to be solved. These problems may be solved by scientists or other groups, such as politicians and economists.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="400bb0ec6791fa56d8a2f5ad85dcc556">
                <text>Which is the most appropriate group to solve each of the problems listed in the following table?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="9d80fd4402d51ef09a269feea8445c27">
                <text>Select ‘Scientists’ or ‘Other’ for each problem.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="11c2081ff371174ffeaaf9fb62bdafb1">
                <text>
                    <b>Scientists</b>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="1f1b19f73bd8a1f295804e2c54d643a4">
                <text>
                    <b>Other</b>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="aa033a662de55e861c96e686c634b059">
                <text>Electric vehicles are often charged using electricity generated by fossil fuels because it is technologically complex to ensure the use of renewable energy.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="c43b0dcd44a8a4ed4ebb440259513b87">
                <text>Electric vehicles are unaffordable for most people.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="298964e1a719ba11c3ea1a6562ec7ad8">
                <text>Industries involved with fossil-fuel vehicles are shrinking, causing people to lose their jobs.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="41d7dfbdcbd52d0291f40ac9541571a4">
                <text>Electric vehicles cannot travel long distances.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
